  "prompt": "What is the temperature on the planet Mercury at the demarcation point between light and dark?",
  "response": "The temperature on Mercury at the terminator, the line demarcating the day and night sides, varies significantly due to the extreme temperature differences between the day and night sides of the planet. On the sunlit side, temperatures can soar up to about 430\u00b0C (about 800\u00b0F), while on the dark side, temperatures can plummet to as low as -180\u00b0C (about -290\u00b0F). At the terminator itself, the temperature would be somewhere between these extremes, but it's still subject to rapid change due to Mercury's lack of a substantial atmosphere to distribute heat. Thus, the exact temperature can vary depending on local conditions and the specific location on the terminator.",
